I don’t know if you’ll see this under the huge amount of comments but ever since your 101 smash bros series you have always made me laugh, and brought some joy into my life when I needed it most. I’m so happy that you found a career that you love doing so much, and I can see in your videos that you are so passionate about what you do... and it’s inspiring honestly. While yeah you are an attractive internet funny man, you also really touch people’s hearts, like my own, in unexpected ways, and I hope you always stay proud of that. If the stars align and I get the chance to meet you one day, I would be overjoyed, but aye, who knows

I have no idea what compelled me to write this all of the sudden. If you’re reading this... whenever I guess, just know I think you’re an amazing person and keep making people happy :)

Also a question: Do you ever fear of growing TOO big as an internet celebrity and feeling overburdened?

snippet.textDisplay:
Okay so like; I've been watching your content for a few ears now, always been basically infatuated with how you present yourself in video, your humor, and your personality as a whole. And I'll admit, I've kinda grown a little out of touch, the past few months. But, I saw this in my recommended feed, clicked on it, and just, wow... I felt something rekindle, inspiration, a old love for a piece of myself that I haven't really been able to access recently. Been playing smash a good 5-10 hours a day, praying I can get good enough to support my family through it. And I feel after watching this video, I remembered why you mean so much to me as a creator, and as a personality. One that I may never have the chance to meet, and just say hi to.

So, thank you. For this video rekindling my love for your content. Thank you for your content as a whole. Thank you for keeping me gazing at the light at the end of the tunnel.
